UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. Kevin Eugene DOW, Defendant-Appellant. No. 06-20369

Conference Calendar.

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Feb. 14, 2007. James Lee Turner, Assistant U.S. Attorney, U.S. Attorney’s Office, Southern District of Texas, Houston, TX, for Plaintiff-Appellee. Larry Chris lies, Rockport, TX, for Defendant-Appellant.

Before BARKSDALE, GARZA, and CLEMENT, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM: *

Counsel appointed to represent Kevin Eugene Dow has filed a motion to withdraw and a brief pursuant to Anders v. California, 386 U.S. 738, 87 S.Ct. 1396, 18 L.Ed.2d 493 (1967). Dow has not filed a response. Our independent review of the brief and the record discloses no nonfrivolous issue. Accordingly, the motion for leave to withdraw is GRANTED, counsel is excused from further responsibilities herein, and the APPEAL IS DISMISSED. See 5th Cir. R. 42.2.

Pursuant to 5th Cir. R. 47.5, the court has determined that this opinion should not be published and is not precedent except under the limited circumstances set forth in 5th Cir. R. 47.5.4.
